# Homebuy visuals

- Dark near-black + cyan hierarchy. Neon is a **priority signal**, not decoration.
- L1 (always emissive): focused field, primary CTA, active tab; brand wordmark.
- L2: library card border glow on hover only (one hover language). Add form card stays flat.
- L3: chips/meta — no glow. Amber only for HOA ≥ $400.
- Fonts: **Akira Expanded** = street address + brand; **Creato Display** = body/UI/price/Gemini prose. Self-hosted under `app/static/fonts/`.
- Gemini sections: `.hb-section-title` + `.hb-gemini-prose`; in-tab Ask/Regenerate on Neighborhood + Financials; empty prompts use `.hb-empty-state`.
- Library: street is the hero; price is quieter Creato under it; thumb stretches to match text column height; address clamps and cards stack under ~800px.
- Density: tighter gaps; dense outlined fields on Add/Filter; never hide listing chips to save space.
- Page chrome: `.hb-page-title` / `.hb-page-meta` / `.hb-empty-state` — don’t leave Quasar `text-h5` / grey helpers on library shell.
- Controls: **black neo faces** on all buttons (never cyan/primary fill). Default label = muted grey; `.hb-btn-cta` = cyan text. Tabs + map chips same language. Props use `color=dark` so Quasar doesn’t paint `--q-primary`.
- Focus: one cyan focus ring on buttons/fields — don’t invent a second glow system.
- Do not introduce purple-on-white or cream-terracotta defaults; stay on the existing token set in `theme.py`.
